  "audio_duration_secs": 52.95,
  "text": "Getting audio to look good usually means bouncing between players, plugins, and export tools. Visualizer keeps it in one place: drop in a track or open the mic, and it turns sound into motion across seven canvas2D modes.\n\nWhat makes it feel solid is that it\u2019s not just reacting to volume. Beat detection tracks spectral flux, the BPM readout settles into something usable, and the stem-band sliders let you decide whether the visuals should follow the sub, the bass, or the brighter stuff on top. Swap between eight palettes and the colour shifts ease over instead of snapping, so you can keep exploring without breaking the flow.\n\nIf you\u2019re working from files, it pulls in title, artist, and album art automatically. If you\u2019re performing live, the mic input has its own sensitivity control. And when something finally lands, you can grab a PNG or kick out a five-second 9:16 WebM loop in one click.\n\nSo instead of fiddling with setup, you get a visual that actually keeps up with the sound and is ready to share.",
  "asr_text": "Getting audio to look good usually means bouncing between players, plugins, and export tools. Visualizer keeps it in one place. Drop in a track or open the mic, and it turns sound into motion across seven canvas 2D modes. What makes it feel solid is that it's not just reacting to volume. Beat detection tracks spectral flux. The BPM readout settles into something usable. And the stem band sliders let you decide whether the visuals should follow the sub, the bass, or the brighter stuff on top. Swap between eight palettes and the color shifts ease over instead of snapping, so you can keep exploring without breaking the flow. If you're working from files, it pulls in title, artist, and album art automatically. If you're performing live, the mic input has its own sensitivity control. And when something finally lands, you can grab a PNG or kick out a 5-second 916 WebM loop in one click. So instead of fiddling with setup, you get a visual that actually keeps up with the sound and is ready to share.",
